div.p: STICKLEBACK, in ichthyology. See Gaste- Foot-STICKS, in printing, slips oſ wood that lie between the foot of the page and the chase, to which they are wedged faſt by the quoins, to keep the form firm, in conjunction with the ſide-ſticks, which are placed at the side of the page, and fixed in the same manner by means of quoins.
